02/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian Patriarch Irinej sent Easter greetings to all Serbs on Thursday (April 1st). Referring to Kosovo, Irinej said in his message that the Serbian Orthodox Church is praying that peace and freedom return to the Serbian "spiritual cradle". He urged Serbs in Kosovo to stay united. Irinej also sent Easter greetings to Roman Catholic Archbishop of Belgrade, Stanislav Hocevar. This year Orthodox, Catholic and Protestant Christians mark the holiday on the same day. (Beta, B92, Tanjug, AP - 01/04/10)
